title.rendered: What is jQuery?

content.rendered: jQuery is not a programming language but a well written JavaScript code. It is a JavaScript code, which do document traversing, event handling, Ajax interactions and Animations.

excerpt.rendered: jQuery is not a programming language but a well written JavaScript code. It is a JavaScript code, which do document traversing, event handling, Ajax interactions and Animations.

title.rendered: Why jQuery is needed?

content.rendered:
jQuery is needed for the following list:

  • Used to develop browser compatible web applications
  • Improve the performance of an application
  • Very fast and extensible
  • UI related functions are written in minimal lines of codes

excerpt.rendered: jQuery is needed for the following list: Used to develop browser compatible web applications Improve the performance of an application Very fast and extensible UI related functions are written in minimal lines of codes

title.rendered: Whether jQuery HTML work for both HTML and XML documents?

content.rendered: No, jQuery HTML only works for HTML documents not for XML Documents.

title.rendered: What are the methods used to provide effects?

content.rendered:
Some of the effects methods are:

  • Toggle()
  • FadeIn() and
  • FadeOut()

title.rendered: What is the advantage of using minimized version of jQuery?

content.rendered: Efficiency of web page increases when minimized version of jQuery is used.min.js file will be more than 50% less than the normal js file. Reduction in the file size makes the web page faster.

title.rendered: What is the difference between find and children methods?

content.rendered: Find method is used to find all levels down the DOM tree but children find single level down the DOM tree.

title.rendered: What is jQuery connect?

content.rendered: A ‘ jQuery connect’ is a plugin used to connect or bind a function with another function. Connect is used to execute function from any other function or plugin is executed.
